data.chText: 一通上电流，这块板就会有磁性。
data.enText: The block becomes magnetic when the current is switched on.
connected with or produced by magnetism
a magnetic disk (= one containing magnetic tape that stores information to be used by a computer)

data.chText: 富有吸引力的；有魅力的
data.enText: that people find very powerful and attractive

tr: possessing an extraordinary ability to attract
having the properties of a magnet
i.e. of attracting iron or steel
example: the hard disk is covered with a thin coat of magnetic material
the needle of a magnetic compass points to the magnetic north pole

tr: of or relating to or caused by magnetism

value.def: If something metal is magnetic, it acts like a magnet.
You use magnetic to describe something that is caused by or relates to the force of magnetism.

example.ex: The electrically charged gas particles are affected by magnetic forces.
example.tran: 带电气体粒子会受磁力影响。
由于磁力而吸在一起的金属碎片。

value.def: You use magnetic to describe tapes and other objects which have a coating of a magnetic substance and contain coded information that can be read by computers or other machines.
If you describe something as magnetic, you mean that it is very attractive to people because it has unusual, powerful, and exciting qualities.

example.ex: ...the magnetic effect of the prosperous German economy on would-be immigrants.
example.tran: 繁荣的德国经济对未来移民的吸引力

example.ex: ...the magnetic pull of his looks and her personality.
example.tran: 他外表的魅力与她个性的魅力

value.tran: 引人注目的;有吸引力的;有魅力的

trans: 磁体媒介(计算机贮存信息的方法)
磁暴(地球或其他星球等磁场的扰动)
